Very disappointed in myself and my performance. Happy the night ended with a win for @blackiechan_soda, who's worked exceptionally hard for it. (Pictured here doing his best Steve Austin impression.)

This is the longest my hair has ever been. And there's a lot of nuisances with having long hair. Not least of which is it's impractical for getting into a fight. The solution: The War Braids.

It's not a style I intend on rocking year round, but, you've gotta admit, it's a strong look. 

🙊🙉🙈

We're nearing the end of January. I've added to the sleeve. I'm back in the gym. And the ship is ready to set sail. 

Now it's about looking to see what 2023 will bring.

The aim this year is to be more active. That means competing in MMA, Boxing, and BJJ.

Things are already beginning to line up, so watch this space.

🙊🙉🙈

🥋x🏴‍☠️

#CapnJack #MMA #BKFC #BJJ

This last fight camp, for @stefmurraypt, @naha_01, and @blackiechan_soda, was a tough one. All of the fighters involved developed leaps and bounds. And the results of that training were on full display last night at @ukfcmma.

Sat in the corner, with @martyndavidcahill and @batchsportstherapy — the best seats in the house — there was some frustration mixed in with the joy, but, by the end of the night, there was more to be proud of than not.

Special thank you to @coachingbykate for her continued help with S&C. And shout out to the rest of the @fightingfitmanchester crew who turned up in support.

Now, today, I've gotta get my arse back in gear, get the rounds in, and get myself in another fight.

Onwards!

🏴‍☠️

#CapnJack #MMA #FightingFit

Former wrestler Jack Claffey (@mrgentlemanjack), better known as Jack Gallagher, steps into the cage with HEXAGONE MMA on JUNE 03 ! 🥊

For his second pro fight, Jack is more motivated than ever ! 👊
With a first loss in a pro fight and a 2-0 record in amateur mma, he is coming to prove himself ! 

🇫🇷 He will face the French @yassin_chtatou, a big striker, with a professional record of 22-5 in K1. 

Quite a novice in mma, he quickly caught up in wrestling, even if his favourite style is striking ! 👊

📣 This promises to be a very interesting fight !

📆 See you at the @arenesbeziers on June 3rd for the HEXAGONE MMA 8 !

Take your ticket now (price from 29€ onwards) :

It's been a weird month. And as we're closing in on the last days of May and moving into June, the next fight is appearing on the horizon.

June 3rd, @hexagonemmafr, I'll be stepping into Béziers Arena in France, a historic venue that's hosted bullfights, concerts, and now MMA.

Bring me that horizon.

🙈🙉🙊

🏴‍☠️x🇫🇷

#MMA #CapnJack #France

Behind the scenes.

This week has been the last week of hard training. I've been kicked, punched, thrown, strangled, stretched, and otherwise been made uncomfortable for a little over a month now.

Next week I'm flying to France, weighing in at Featherweight, fighting for @hexagonemmafr, and showing the fruits of not only my labour, but the team we're building at @fightingfitmanchester. 

The event will be streaming on @dazn_mma. So if you can't be there in person, you can still be present virtually!

🏴‍☠️x🇫🇷

📸@leehamiltoncooper

#MMA #CapnJack #France

In case you missed the news — first of all, how dare you — my fight has been delayed. As a matter of fact, the entire @hexagonemmafr card has been delayed.

Concerns over the weather have forced a change in date. What that new date is, right now, is uncertain. As soon as I know, you'll know. Such are the dangers when you're competing in a bull fighting arena.

It's something completely out of my control, though that doesn't make it any easier to accept. Getting the news half way into weight cut week meant it hit especially hard. But I've had some carbs now, and a coffee, and if you know me, you know that can make a world of difference to my mood.

Keep those eyes and apps open for updates as they come.

c'est la vie

🏴‍☠️x🇫🇷

📸@leehamiltoncooper

#CapnJack

FIGHT UPDATE:

Today was supposed to be fight day. I'd intended on lounging around Southern France, eating a croissant, and sipping a cappuccino. Y'know, the hard life.

Instead, the event has been moved to the 4th of August, so we're going back to camp for another eight weeks of fun and fists to the face. I improved a lot in the lead up to today. I'm only going to be better come fight night.

The date may have changed, but the result will remain the same. I will have my croissants!

🏴‍☠️x🇫🇷

📸@leehamiltoncooper

I've been a busy bee recently. I've been in camp, I've been coaching, but I haven't been competing!

Fight date has moved to August 4th — @hexagonemmafr, Arènes de Béziers.

I wanted to be a bit more active this year. And, although I have been, outside of the cage, I still haven't made that walk once. 

Hopefully August is the first of three fights this year and then it's onto the next one!

That's three weeks of training, a day of travel, around fourty-eight hours of dehydration, a moment or two to weigh-in, a brief but wonderful refeed, and then however long it takes my pasty legs to take me from backstage to the cage.

Easy enough.

We're a little more than two weeks out from @hexagonemmafr 8 and the conclusion of what has seemed, at times, like the fight camp with no end. Weight is on point — if you couldn't tell by looking. White as a slice of Warburton's and twice as cut.

If you'd like to look as jacked as @muskettjames does in that @xmartialofficial rashguard, then click the link in my profile, peruse their store, and be sure to use the coupon code CAPNJACK at checkout. #CapnJack #MMA #BJJ #MuayThai #LethalWeapon

The last seven days of hard training before fight week shenanigans. Glad that I don't have to become Jack Skellington to make the weight this time.

Having an opponent change, along with the date, has made this feel like two distinct camps, rather than one long one. Only without the win on the record, the financial reward, or the post-weigh-in food orgy – y'know the gratifying stuff – in between.

It's been good to be busy, though. Looking to stay busy afterwards, too.

Calories ✅
Caffeine ✅
Croissants ... SOON

Full Monty reboot is looking promising.

Finished my final session before flying out to France next week for @hexagonemmafr.

It's been a good few months of preparation. A special thanks goes out to @coachingbykate for not only her excellent organizational skills and S&C programming, but monitoring intensity levels and helping avoid burnout throughout.

The aim with my fights has always been the accruing of experience (like a real life JRPG) and going back-to-back with camps was something new.

With training done, there's only the weight cut, then the actual fighting left!

Fight went well. France was fun. I'm exhausted. A good number of people put a lot of time into not only one but two consecutive camps. I'm glad to have made a good account of their efforts.

Thank you to @hexagonemmafr for having me on the show.

They ran an incredibly well organised event. The venue was, of course, incredible; it was one of the more unique things I've taken part in. Hopefully not my last time fighting in France. (The crowd loved me.)

Shout out to @thejunglemma for loaning me @sebas.bjj for the night.

I appreciate all the messages I've received over the last few days. Thanks for enduring me spamming your feeds in return.
